FeedPackage.Description:
MyCouch is the simple asynchronous CouchDb and Cloudant client for .Net - builds on top of the asynchronous HTTP client and uses JSON.Net to provide flexible serialization behaviour. It tries to keep the domain language of CouchDb instead of bringing in generic repositories and other confusing stuff. MyCouch lets you work with raw JSON and/or entities/POCOS without requiring any implementation of interfaces, baseclasses etc. MyCouch provides you with some model conventions like injection of $doctype to the document. It is plug-gable. If you don't like some piece, then hook in your implementation instead.
If you want Cloudant specific features like Lucene Searches, go with the "MyCouch.Cloudant" package instead.
Supports .Net4.0, .Net4.5 and Windows store apps 8.1 (WinRT).
Please NOTE. This is not an official Cloudant package.
Please NOTE. If you don't have NuGet up to date, some uses has had issues with resolving dependencies.

It tries to keep the domain language of CouchDb and lets you work with requests and responses but also provides you with an alternative simplifying async API. MyCouch lets you work with raw JSON and/or entities/POCOS without requiring any implementation of interfaces or base-classes etc. MyCouch provides you with some model conventions like injection of $doctype to the document. It is pluggable. If you don't like some piece, then hook in your implementation instead.
Supports .Net4.0, .Net4.5 and Windows store 8.0 and 8.1 (WinRT).

This package contains support for Cloudant specific features. If you want pure CouchDb support and basic Cloudant support, go with the "MyCouch" package instead.
MyCouch is the simple asynchronous CouchDb and Cloudant client for .Net - builds on top of the asynchronous HTTP client and uses JSON.Net to provide flexible serialization behaviour. It tries to keep the domain language of CouchDb instead of bringing in generic repositories and other confusing stuff. MyCouch lets you work with raw JSON and/or entities/POCOS without requiring any implementation of interfaces, baseclasses etc. MyCouch provides you with some model conventions like injection of $doctype to the document. It is plug-gable. If you don't like some piece, then hook in your implementation instead.
Supports .Net4.0, .Net4.5 and Windows store apps (WinRT).

Please NOTE. If you don't have NuGet up to date, some uses has had issues with resolving dependencies.

FeedPackage.Title: MyCouch.Cloudant

FeedPackage.Description:
This package contains support for Cloudant specific features. If you want pure CouchDb support go with the "MyCouch" package instead.
MyCouch is the simple asynchronous CouchDb and Cloudant client for .Net - building on top of the asynchronous HTTP client and uses JSON.Net to provide flexible serialization behaviour. It tries to keep the domain language of CouchDb and lets you work with requests and responses but also provides you with an alternative simplifying async API. MyCouch lets you work with raw JSON and/or entities/POCOS without requiring any implementation of interfaces or base-classes etc. MyCouch provides you with some model conventions like injection of $doctype to the document. It is plug-gable. If you don't like some piece, then hook in your implementation instead.
Supports .Net4.0, .Net4.5 and Windows store apps 8.1 (WinRT).
Please NOTE. If you don't have NuGet up to date, some users has experienced issues with resolving dependencies.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Can be found on project site: https://github.com/danielwertheim/mycouch/wiki/release-notes

This scenario is common for integration tests running HTTP requests in isolation.
